<paragraph id="681D3C28B74A3DB759B79690F70AF759" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C163FCF25FE9450E16AFCCF266DE6CC9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="19D03E4D018040B90B92D646B2A8904C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum torvum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="torvum">
<emphasis id="06D872B97D0D704FD05361E901A00AB4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum torvum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is naturalised throughout tropical Asia; it is native to Central America and the Caribbean but has achieved a worldwide distribution in tropical and subtropical areas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
